 Project chemical rocket developments forward (with some wishful thinking thrown in):<br>
 So we lose a Sea Dragon (or Ares or Shuttle-C or whatever) or 5 for every hundred we send up. Cargos are insured, and the utility of sending up a big load on a BDB makes it still worthwhile.<br>
Crews are never risked, and a recoverable spaceplane is the only crew ride aside from the Soyuz.<br>
